20:47.987 --> 20:54.133
would come to watch A&M play, and I'd stay over in 
the dorm with a guy named Cecil Ballew, who played

20:54.822 --> 21:00.068
baseball here, who was later dean of men at 
Crawford State University. And I'd come down to

21:00.088 --> 21:10.260
them, and I came to A&M and watched some football 
games, and I got where I could tell each player just

21:00.088 --> 21:10.260
by the way he walked. You can't do that today. But 
they had some individual deals about them. So when

21:15.827 --> 21:22.635
I was being recruited by several schools, and I 
didn't know what to do, and I went to Rice because

21:23.729 --> 21:36.103
they recruited me strongly and actually a guy had 
offered me some help that his brother-in-law was

21:23.729 --> 21:36.103
mayor of Stephenville at that time. And so I went 
down there but it didn't turn out so I came back up

21:36.123 --> 21:39.147
here. The first time I just came down was Derrick 
Moser's parents. Right and so and you enrolled in

21:42.410 --> 21:45.033
the fall of? 1941. 41 and A&M's football program 
was very, very, very strong then. Yeah we won the

21:50.640 --> 21:53.483
conference that year and had won it. 39 were the 
champions. 40, they won it in 41. But in 38, they

21:58.467 --> 22:00.349
nearly got fired. If it hadn't been for Bert 
Clopper, it would have been, because he came to

